<br>
Many of us that have all ready reached the higher levels have gotten our stats and resists to levels, where more may or may not serve any significant purpous.  It gets quite difficult to tell.<br>
<br>
This leaves us with the 5 skills at the bottom.<br>
- First Aid, while handy, requires bandages, and its not something that helps us during a prolonged fight.<br>
- Natural Lung Capacity, most at this point have Enduring Breath items.<br>
- Improved Natural Metabolism, sounds kinda cool, but its not going to help my character be more efficient, except to be able to hold more loot inplace of food.<br>
<br>
That leaves us with Natural Run Speed and Natural Regeneration.  Anyone with Jboots will probably run as fast or faster than someone with the runs speed ability maxed.  VI has stated that the run speed won't be as fast as sow.  I can see this being a great bonus indoors, but that means its only working a portion of the time.  Not to mention that max skilling in both of these abilities would be needed to gain access to the Archetype Abilities.  This leaves us with Natural Regeneration, admitidly not the most usefull thing in the world, but with a maxed ability in this you will be gaining an extra 3 hps every 6 seconds, in addition to any other regen you might have working for you (natural plus items).  Overall in long fight sequences where area damage takes place this can add up to a significant mana savings for the people trying to keep us alive.  As I see it, part of a rogue's job is to try not to take damage, while dispensing as much as possible.  It just seems logical that any damage we can restore faster would only benifit the party or raid overall.<br>
<br>
If I remember correctly there was a post a while back, about how many rogues were wearing fungi tunics when on raids, because it made a noticable impact in how much mana the healers had to devote to keeping the rogue alive when that mana could have been spent on healing a more primary tank.<br>
<br>
The reason why not to continue the regen enhancment in the Archetype ability section is that many of those abilities appear to be more advantageous. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udietrichsoulpiercer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dietrich SoulPiercer</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/01 2:44:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8844.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> XP per point.</span><hr size=1> From actually Playing.....<br>
